article.headline: Gauchos turn the ball over 27 times
article.linkText: Colorado State pulls upset against No. 23  Santa Barbara
article.story:
FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Jasai Ferrucho scored 13 points, and
Colorado State controlled play in the second half to upset 
UC Santa Barbara (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP)  55-44 Sunday night.

	   After shooting a dismal .190 while making just four of 21 shots
in the first half, the Rams (7-4) were 14-for-28 over the final 20
minutes. They overcame a 20-15 halftime deficit and outscored the
Gauchos (5-2) 40-24 after the break.

	   Lindsay Taylor led UCSB with 13 points, and Lisa Willett added
11. But the Gauchos committed 22 fouls in the game, were outshot
from the line 17-4 and turned the ball over 27 times to just 17 for
Colorado State.

	   Ferrucho was 4-for-6 from the floor and 5-for-7 from the line
for the Rams, who also got 14 points from Elizabeth English. She
made three of 11 shots and was 7-for-7 from the line.
